Subject: dwg_set_next_objhandle: don't reuse a stale next_hdl that collides

A freshly ezdxf-authored drawing (IngeCAD "new drawing" + a couple of
entities) produced a DWG that AutoCAD/BricsCAD/ODA refused to open:
"Object of class AcDbRegAppTableRecord / AcDbBlockTableRecord can't be cast
to AcDbEntity". Cause: the encoder adds table records after DXF import
(the "LibreDWG"/ACAD_MLEADERVER/AcadAnnotative APPIDs for the r2018->r2000
downconvert). dwg_set_next_objhandle honored dwg->next_hdl verbatim when
set, WITHOUT checking the object_map, so a stale next_hdl left over from
import landed on a handle already owned by another table record (e.g. an
LTYPE at handle B) -> two objects share a handle -> the handle map is
ambiguous and a table record resolves where an entity is expected.

Only reuse next_hdl when it is still free (or already maps to this same
object); otherwise fall through to a fresh handseed. Real bench (dwg2dxf
sourced) files are unaffected; every freshly-created ezdxf drawing now
opens. 254 unit tests green.

Co-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

--- a/src/dwg.c
+++ b/src/dwg.c
@@ dwg_set_next_objhandle
   if (dwg->next_hdl)
     {
-      obj->handle.value = dwg->next_hdl;
-      dwg_set_handle_size (&obj->handle);
-      hash_set (dwg->object_map, obj->handle.value, (uint64_t)obj->index);
-      dwg->next_hdl = 0;
-      return;
+      uint64_t existing = dwg->object_map
+                              ? hash_get (dwg->object_map, dwg->next_hdl)
+                              : HASH_NOT_FOUND;
+      if (existing == HASH_NOT_FOUND || existing == (uint64_t)obj->index)
+        {
+          obj->handle.value = dwg->next_hdl;
+          dwg_set_handle_size (&obj->handle);
+          if (!dwg->object_map)
+            dwg->object_map = hash_new (200);
+          hash_set (dwg->object_map, obj->handle.value, (uint64_t)obj->index);
+          dwg->next_hdl = 0;
+          return;
+        }
+      dwg->next_hdl = 0; /* stale/colliding: use a fresh handseed below */
     }
